               -  below we rely on the fact that the Italian stemmer turns all forms of
               -  avere, dare, essere, fare and stare back to the infinitive. In generating
               -  the stemmed stopword list we only need to mention the infinitive form.

avere          -  to have
               -  dare (to give) not stopped
essere         -  to be
fare           -  to do
stare          -  to be, stand

               -  single letter forms:

a              -  at
c              -  as c' for ce or ci
e              -  and, is (with grave accent)
i              -  the
l              -  as l'
o              -  or



